race.comment: ORTHIES (3) started favourite but was a little one-paced when resuming over 1200m at Kembla last start. Suited out to 1300m and from a good gate will get all the favours in running. Should bounce back and play a major role. ALIGNED (8) raced handy then launched a strong challenge only to miss by the barest margin over 1200m at Newcastle last time out. Going very well and like the engagement of Rawiller. Poses a genuine threat. UNREAL EXPECTATION (7) is a four-year-old back from a nine-week break and faces the starter for just the sixth time. Progressed to be competitive at provincial level at the close of the maiden prep. Good enough to get involved here despite the gap between runs. BEND THE KNEE (4) finished alongside ORTHIES when they clashed at Kembla recently. That was the veterans first outing in 18 weeks. Fitter and should be thereabouts again. PRESIDENT (1) is back in grade and fitter for three runs back from a spell so keep him very safe.
